## ‚öôÔ∏è Setup

### **Step 1: Configure Git Aliases**

Add these to your `~/.gitconfig`:

```ini
[alias]
  # Quick status
  s = status -sb
  
  # Better log
  lg = log --oneline --graph --decorate --all
  
  # Quick add and commit
  ac = !git add -A && git commit -m
  
  # Undo last commit (keep changes)
  undo = reset HEAD~1 --soft
  
  # Clean merged branches
  cleanup = !git branch --merged | grep -v '\\*' | xargs -n 1 git branch -d
  
  # Show changed files
  changed = diff --name-only
```

### **Step 2: Create Git Scripts**

Create `~/bin/git-scripts/`:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/bin/git-scripts
```

**Smart Commit Script** (`~/bin/git-scripts/smart-commit.sh`):

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Smart commit with conventional commit format

read -p "Type (feat/fix/docs/refactor): " type
read -p "Scope (optional): " scope
read -p "Description: " desc

if [ -n "$scope" ]; then
  git commit -m "${type}(${scope}): ${desc}"
else
  git commit -m "${type}: ${desc}"
fi
```

Make it executable:
```bash
chmod +x ~/bin/git-scripts/smart-commit.sh
```

### **Step 3: Set Up Git Hooks**

**Pre-commit Hook** (`.git/hooks/pre-commit`):

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Run linting and tests before commit

echo "Running pre-commit checks..."

# Run linter
npm run lint
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "‚ùå Linting failed. Please fix errors before committing."
  exit 1
fi

# Run type check
npm run type-check
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "‚ùå Type check failed. Please fix errors before committing."
  exit 1
fi

echo "‚úÖ Pre-commit checks passed!"
exit 0
```

Make it executable:
```bash
chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit
```

