## üéØ Usage

### **Daily Workflow**

```bash
# 1. Quick status
git s

# 2. Add and commit with alias
git ac "Add new feature"

# 3. Use smart commit script
~/bin/git-scripts/smart-commit.sh
# Type: feat
# Scope: auth
# Description: Add JWT authentication
# Result: git commit -m "feat(auth): Add JWT authentication"

# 4. View commit history
git lg

# 5. Clean up merged branches
git cleanup
```

### **Branch Management**

```bash
# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/new-feature

# Work on changes...
git ac "Implement feature X"

# Push and create PR
git push -u origin feature/new-feature

# After merge, cleanup
git checkout main
git pull
git cleanup  # Removes merged branches
```

