## üîß Advanced Automation

### **Automated Branch Naming**

```bash
# ~/.gitconfig
[alias]
  new-feature = "!f() { git checkout -b feature/$1; }; f"
  new-hotfix = "!f() { git checkout -b hotfix/$1; }; f"
```

Usage:
```bash
git new-feature user-authentication
# Creates and checks out: feature/user-authentication

git new-hotfix critical-bug
# Creates and checks out: hotfix/critical-bug
```

### **Commit Message Templates**

Create `.gitmessage`:

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>

# Type: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore
# Scope: Component or module affected
# Subject: Brief description (imperative mood)
# Body: Detailed explanation (optional)
# Footer: Breaking changes, issue references (optional)
```

Configure Git to use it:
```bash
git config --global commit.template ~/.gitmessage
```

